About
-----
This plugin for OJS 2 provides a set of syndication feeds for the current issue in RSS1.0/RDF and Atom formats.  Feed links are embedded into the HTML header for the current issue and are available to all RSS/Atom-aware browsers and aggregators as per standard web specifications.

License
-------
This plugin is licensed under the GNU General Public License v2. See the file COPYING for the complete terms of this license.

System Requirements
-------------------
Same requirements as the OJS 2.2 core.

Installation
------------
To install the plugin:
 - enable the plugin by going to:  Home > User > Journal Management > Plugin Management  and selecting "ENABLE" under "Feed Plugin"

Configuration
------------
The plugin can be configured to display feed links on all journal pages, or only current issue pages.

Known Issues
------------
- Improperly-formatted (non-RFC2822) email addresses within OJS articles or contact addresses may cause invalid feeds to be generated.
- Articles with no abstract (eg. editorials) will create Atom warnings due to lack of entry:content or entry:summary elements
- Multiple articles with the same publish date/time (eg. in an issue) may create an Atom warning

